President Trump signed a bipartisan bill to fully reauthorize the 9/11 Victims Compensation Fund in a ceremony held at the White House. The bill provides permanent financial support for families who lost loved ones in the September 11th attacks and pensions for those suffering from cancer and other illnesses related to the attacks. The President expressed his gratitude to the first responders and families of the fallen heroes, acknowledging their sacrifice and dedication. He also extended condolences to the families affected by the recent shooting in Gilroy, California. The President signed the bill into law and invited the families and first responders to join him on stage.